survey.answer: Easy to do, but a bit confusing to understand how to connect sounds with colours.
I experience tinnitus sometimes but not after this experiment. I like the second task which requires users to adjust the sound base on the displayed color. Interesting! :)
It seemed like the first part sounds were repeating, I had an impression it was 4 sounds only

Trying to tie sounds to colour hues was a bit abstract for me. I mostly tied sounds to saturation and luminosity. 
It should be noted that my brain filters out tinnitus most of the time. The only time I can hear it is directly when remembering that I have it or when the word itself is mentioned.

Czesc Sabina! 🐱‍👤

Oto moj feedback:
* Label znikaja ze sliderow (sa tylko widoczne na pierwszym ekranie w kazdej kategori)
* Kontrole co sa w kazym rogu sa troche daleko i ciezko je dostrzec
* Chcialbym miec przycisk play na srodku, bo go czesto uzywalem. 
* Po jakims czasiw to zaczal dziwk u mnie troche trzeszczesc, ale to moze byc spowodowane karta dziekowa albo tym ze uzywam Firefox. 
* W perwszej czesci niektore dzwieki byly wylosowane dwa razy, jeden po drugim. 
* Torche duzo zadan. Na poczatku nie dostrzeglem licznika zadan co by w rogu.

It may be interesting after the test to get some summary or hypothesis of how sound and color are linked. Or how people generally perceive sound and color together. That way the participant can also reflect on the answers given and how they compare to what they then read. Gives a little bit back to the user in a "Oh, I never knew that" type of revelation. It could also just be me not knowing more about the subject.
Note: I have a mild protanomaly colourblindness and am somewhat tone-deaf
Choosing the different sounds and colors was fun and a cool experience. I would suggest shortening the survey a bit to avoid participant fatigue.
Second part is a good idea!
I've never really thought about the link between colors and sound, but evidently, I do associate different sounds with different colors...
Good luck! I hope you get interesting results!
there was a lot of noise when I adjust the sound and in the last 5 to 6 questions, there was no sound any more.
Users should be asked to turn off any blue-light blocking applications as it might interfere with the color perception.
